label.value: Cleavage at junction of stratum corneum and stratum granulosum

Granulomas are small 0.5 to 2 mm collections of modified macrophages called epithelioid cells usually surrounded by lymphocytes.
A benign (noncancerous) tumorlike malformation made up of an abnormal mixture of cells and tissues that originates in the ureter.

definition.value: Detection of DNA and RNA originating from an infectious agent (bacteria, viruses, parasites and fungi) in the urine.
